4 TYPES->static,relative,absolute,fixed

1.STATIC->this position is the default
2.RELATIVE->positioning relative to the default
3.ABSOLUTE->positioning relative to the nearest positioned ancestor
4.FIXED->positioning relative to the top left corner of browser window

sample code

 .blue-box{
      position: relative;
      height: 300px;
      width: 500px;
      background-color: blue;
      top: 200px;
      left: 200px;
    }
    .red-circle{
      position: absolute;
      background-color: red;
      width: 200px;
      height: 200px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      top: 150px;
      left: 250px;
    }
